Avoid distributing tests & other unnecessary files

HitHighlighter Class: avoid PHP 8 errors

This change should avoid such errors:
PHP Fatal error: Uncaught ArgumentCountError: array_merge() does not accept unknown named parameters

call_user_func_array() expects a function name and an array of parameters to be unpacked and passed on to the function.
In PHP 8, when call_user_func_array() receives an array of parameters with string keys, the keys will be interpreted as parameter names.
Opt for an alternative to spread to be compatible with PHP 5.3.

comment.body:
@k1LoW
If `deploymentBucket.name` is written with an empty string (it is default value), the configuration file validation will detect the following warning:

```
Warning: Invalid configuration encountered
  at 'provider.deploymentBucket.name': must NOT have fewer than 3 characters
  at 'provider.deploymentBucket.name': must match pattern "(?!^(\d{1,3}\.){3}\d{1,3}$)(^(([a-z0-9]|[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*[a-z0-9])\.)*([a-z0-9]|[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*[a-z0-9])$)"
```

This is a validation-only issue, and the internal code of the Serverless Framework seems to treat `deploymentBucket.name` as null if it is an empty string.

https://github.com/serverless/serverless/blob/bb37f4fe75ff5234fae48ada433cd52ddf51cb91/lib/plugins/aws/provider.js#L221-L232
https://github.com/serverless/serverless/blob/bb37f4fe75ff5234fae48ada433cd52ddf51cb91/lib/plugins/aws/provider.js#L898-L919

To avoid this warning, users need to specify the `deploymentBucket`, because S3 bucket name is should be globally unique, the default value cannot be set.

I have determined that there are few use cases where `deploymentBucket` must be explicitly specified, so I removed the configuration value.

comment.body:
@k1LoW
If `deploymentBucket.name` is written with an empty string (it is default value), the configuration file validation will detect the following warning:

```
Warning: Invalid configuration encountered
  at 'provider.deploymentBucket.name': must NOT have fewer than 3 characters
  at 'provider.deploymentBucket.name': must match pattern "(?!^(\d{1,3}\.){3}\d{1,3}$)(^(([a-z0-9]|[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*[a-z0-9])\.)*([a-z0-9]|[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*[a-z0-9])$)"
```

This is a validation-only issue, and the internal code of the Serverless Framework seems to treat `deploymentBucket.name` as null if it is an empty string.

https://github.com/serverless/serverless/blob/bb37f4fe75ff5234fae48ada433cd52ddf51cb91/lib/plugins/aws/provider.js#L221-L232
https://github.com/serverless/serverless/blob/bb37f4fe75ff5234fae48ada433cd52ddf51cb91/lib/plugins/aws/provider.js#L898-L919

To avoid this warning, users need to specify the `deploymentBucket`, because S3 bucket name is should be globally unique, the default value cannot be set.

I have determined that there are few use cases where `deploymentBucket` must be explicitly specified, so I removed the configuration value.
